column49: I have been ordering books for at least 25 years. The QR code is not easy for parents who are  technically challenged and/or do not have access to the internet. Yes, there are MANY people in Title I schools without any access to the internet. So every single student brought me money and cut out the a photo of the book they wanted.   I tried ordering books and it was not easy. I input the order where it said "Have a Flyer..." and apparently, that is the parent site, not the teacher part.   Also, DO NOT put a due date. I need to set the due date with my students based on my activities, meetings, etc. I can not be held to a random due date you have created for them and me.   Other teachers and I have talked about this in the lunchroom and this is just not user friendly. When you do the research, please include teachers and students in low income areas of the US and see how difficult it is for these families.
